      <title>At least 14 injured in Japan knife attack</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANA mass stabbing in the city of Kawasaki, Japan on Tuesday morning has left over a dozen school children wounded and one child dead, Japanese broadcaster NHK reports.An elementary school girl and a man in his 30s were believed to have died in the attack, according to The Japan Times.As many as 16 other school children were injured in the attack while waiting at a bus stop, NHK reports. According to Kyodo News, two other adults were also wounded.The news agency cites police as saying that two of the school girls and a woman in her 40s suffered serious injuries because of the attack.The suspect was a man in his 50s, police told Kyodo News. He was seen holding knives in both hands. Police say the suspect stabbed victims before stabbing himself in the neck. Officers later found two knives that were believed to be used during the attack.The children were believed to be students at Cartitas Elementary School. However, according to The Japan Times, officials at the elementary school could not immediately confirm if the victims were their students. They added that they are still gathering information. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1.The city where the attack took place on the map of Japan and 16 school children on lying on the ground, with one of them dead2. An adult male and an elementary school girl believed to have died in the attack3. The victims of the attack waiting at the bus stop4. The suspect holding two knives and two police officers finding the knives where the attack took place VOICEOVER (in English): "A mass stabbing in the city of Kawasaki, near Tokyo on Tuesday morning has left over a dozen school children wounded and at least one dead.""According to The Japan Times, an elementary school girl and a man in his 30s were believed to have died in the attack.""Japanese broadcaster NHK reports 16 other school children were injured in the attack while waiting at a bus stop.""According to Kyodo News, two other adults were also wounded.""The news agency cites police as saying that two of the school girls and a woman in her 40s suffered serious injuries because of the attack.""The suspect was a man in his 50s, police told Kyodo News. He was seen holding knives in both hands.""Police say the suspect stabbed victims before stabbing himself in the neck.""Officers later found two knives that were believed to be used during the attack."SOURCES: Kyodo News, NHK World, Japan Times The Guardian, BBC News, https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2019/05/cd2e013a9973-urgent-11-including-elementary-school-children-stabbed-in-city-near-tokyo.htmlhttps://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20190528_10/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20190528_19/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2019/05/28/national/crime-legal/11-reported-stabbed-kawasaki-including-elementary-school-children/#.XOydSZgzZjUhttps://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/may/28/japan-mass-stabbing-children-among-injured-in-attack-kawasakihttps://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-48428695***]]></description>
